This paper is about vulnerability discovery models in software security, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also introduces quantitative metrics and analyzes the impact of vulnerability data sets, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the suitability of different models for vulnerability discovery, which could be relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
